# Cost of delay {#sec-cost-of-delay}


::: {.cell}

:::



## EUROCONTROL recommended values

The tables below present an overview of the **average cost per minute to the airline of ground or airborne delay of a commercial passenger flight**. Please note that all the numbers are based on studies performed by the 
University of Westminster [@uow:2004] [@uow:2015] and are adjusted to 2022 prices based on
[inflation](#tbl-inflation-table).

The figures presented in this section constitute high-level averages and are
valid as indicative estimates. **It is strongly recommended that they are used as indicators or for general insights into delay costs and not for specific analyses or operational planning.** 
Different values may be obtained for other contexts 
(e.g. other airspace areas or airports (hub or non-hub), etc.), with different 
aircraft and delay distributions.


